claim.claim-text:
1. An examination system, comprising: 
input means for inputting a desired sequence of a plurality of examination methods for a patient; 
changing means for changing the desired sequence into a changed sequence; 
performing means for performing examination in accordance with the changed sequence and obtaining results therefrom; and 
output means for outputting in the desired sequence a plurality of examination results obtained by the performing means.

2. An examination system, comprising: 
input means for inputting examination request information formed of a plurality of examination methods for a patient; 
display means for displaying the examination sequence of the input examination methods in a list; 
handling means for handling the examination method as a plurality of examination method objects and for attaching a status to each examination method object; 
changing means for changing the display format of each examination method object according to the status; 
selection means for selecting one of the examination method objects; 
performing means for performing examination in accordance with the examination conditions determined by the selected examination method object and in accordance with an examination mode determined by the status of the selected examination method object; and 
output means for outputting in a desired sequence a plurality of examined examination method objects.

7. An examination system, comprising: 
input means for inputting an examination request formed of a plurality of examination methods in a desired examination sequence; 
display means for displaying an examination sequence of the input examination methods in a list; 
handling means for handling the examination method as a plurality of examination method objects and for attaching a status to each examination method object; 
format changing means for changing the display format of each examination method object according to the status attached to each examination object; 
sequence changing means for changing the desired examination sequence of the input examination method objects into a changed examination; 
performing means for performing examination in accordance with the examination conditions determined by the examination method object selected on the basis of the changed examination sequence and in accordance with an examination mode determined by the status of the selected examination method object; and 
output means for outputting in the desired examination sequence a plurality of examined examination method objects.

19. A photographic system for irradiating a patient with X-rays and for digitally obtaining an X-ray transmitted image, said photographic system comprising: 
an X-ray photographic apparatus for performing X-ray photography in given examination units; 
an apparatus for inputting, to said X-ray photographic apparatus, patient data and photographic request information from which setting parameters, which are required for said X-ray photographic apparatus to perform photography, can be created; 
operation means for displaying the system status and for performing an operation; 
input means for inputting photographic request information formed of a plurality of photographic requests with respect to one patient data; 
creation means for creating setting parameters required to perform X-ray photography from the plurality of input photographic requests; and 
calling means for calling the created setting parameters.
